    <tr><td>Cross-realm</td><td>Not a concern &mdash; DOM events don't cross iframe boundaries. <code>instanceof</code> is reliable for all DOM event scenarios.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Zero patching</td><td>Yes &mdash; uses existing injector system</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Type safety</td><td>Full &mdash; handler receives typed event from the provided class</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Micro-frontend safe</td><td>Yes &mdash; each MFE brings its own injector scope</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Protocol-based architecture</td><td><strong>Native fit</strong> &mdash; reuses the same provide/resolve pattern used for everything else</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Implementation flexibility</td><td>Full &mdash; different subtrees can provide different event classes for the same protocol</td></tr>
    <tr><td>DevTools</td><td>Normal &mdash; standard addEventListener under the hood</td></tr>
  </tbody>
